"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757796","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>Other than minor or bespoke purchases, the Scotland Office does not normally undertake direct procurement or tendering projects. It uses existing service contracts between suppliers and the Scottish Government, the Ministry of Justice or the Cabinet Office. The Scotland Office do not therefore hold records of the procurement process duration.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-12T12:04:31.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757796/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757796/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757796/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-05","Scotland Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many procurements undertaken by his Department have taken more than (a) three months, (b) six months, (c) one year and (d) two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757797","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Scotland Office does not sub-let its estate, it uses the process of a Memorandum of Terms of Occupation which enables us to use assets efficiently and share space between government organisations.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-12T12:05:10.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757797/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757797/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757797/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-05","Scotland Office: Sub-letting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much his Department has received from sub-lets on its estate in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757798","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave to the hon Member for Ochil and South Perthshire on 6 September 2017, UIN 6224.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-11T12:45:29.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757798/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757798/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757798/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-05","City Region Deals: Stirling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent progress has been made to conclude the heads of agreement with Clackmannanshire Council on the Stirling city region deal.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","8620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757799","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department has amended the process for re-letting franchises so that bidders are now required to give customers who work or commute part-time a better value for money option than buying multiple return journeys.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-11T13:26:22.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757799/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757799/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757799/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Railways: Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent progress he has made in introducing flexible ticketing for part-time commuters.","false","Biography information for James Cartlidge","South Suffolk","James Cartlidge","8612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757800","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>The number of reported road casualties of people aged 70 years and older in reported road accidents in Great Britain in 2011 to 2015 is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Casualties</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>11,824</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>11,469</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>11,292</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>12,181</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>11,761</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source DfT STATS19</p><p> </p><p>Casualties includes all road user types, including pedestrians.</p><p> </p><p>The number of drivers aged 70 years and older involved in reported road accidents in Great Britain in 2011 to 2015 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Drivers involved in accidents</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>11,929</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>11,869</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>12,102</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>12,947</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>12,353</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source DfT STATS19</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-13T10:58:25.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757800/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757800/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757800/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of people aged over 70 who have been involved in a road traffic accident in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","8547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757801","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>The current driver licensing arrangements take into account the risks that an individual poses to road safety and are designed to be fair and proportionate to all drivers who remain fit and competent to drive, regardless of age. Age alone is not a reliable indicator of driving ability.</p><p> </p><p>However, all drivers aged 70 and over must renew their licences and make a declaration about their medical fitness to drive at least every three years. If there is evidence that a driver does not meet the appropriate medical stands, their entitlement to drive is immediately removed.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-12T10:17:36.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757801/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757801/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757801/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Driving Tests: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his policy is on the introduction of compulsory re-examination driving tests for people over the age of 70.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","8546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757802","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>The information requested can only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-13T14:57:44.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757802/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757802/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757802/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Department for Transport: Sub-letting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much his Department has received from sub-lets on its estate in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757803","Department for Transport","true","2017-09-13","<p>My Department reports the following live contracts where procurements have taken more than (a) three months, (b) six months, (c) one year and (d) two years (where data is available).</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>More than</p></td><td><p>DFTc</p></td><td><p>VCA</p></td><td><p>MCA</p></td><td><p>DVLA</p></td><td><p>DVSA</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(a)three months</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>33</p></td><td><p>50</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(b) six months</p></td><td><p>14*</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>22</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(c) one year</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial">2</del><ins class="ministerial">3</ins></p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial">4</del><ins class="ministerial">5</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(d) two years</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>*includes 13 procurements run by Crown Commercial Service on behalf of my department.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-13T14:50:55.933Z","2017-11-07T16:40:03.823Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757803/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757803/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757803/answer","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757803/answer/previousversion/11329","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Department for Transport: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many procurements undertaken by his Department have taken more than (a) three months, (b) six months, (c) one year and (d) two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8765"
