"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757805","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>It will be for the individual bus operators and local councils who have been awarded funding under the Low Emission Bus Scheme to take the final decision as to which companies will manufacture the new buses and for the companies to decide where these will be manufactured.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-12T08:43:25.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757805/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757805/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757805/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Buses: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the announcement of 28 August 2017 on funding for low emission buses, where those buses will be manufactured.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","8804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757806","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>Highways England is currently finalising the Dartford River Crossing accounts for 2016/17 which will be audited by the National Audit Office in October 2017. The 2016/17 figures cannot be provided at this point.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-12T08:57:23.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757806/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757806/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757806/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Dartford-Thurrock Crossing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the cost was of managing the Dartford River Crossing in the last financial year; and what income was received from (a) user charges and (b) penalty notices related to that crossing.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","8856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757807","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>There are currently over 11,500 public chargepoints in the UK including over 900 rapid chargepoints, making this the largest network of rapid charging points for electric vehicles in Europe. Chargepoint provision is increasing all the time; however the Office for Low Emission Vehicles does not make detailed forecasts.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-12T10:13:47.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757807/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757807/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757807/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Electric Vehicles: Charging Points","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many publicly accessible electric car recharging points there are in the UK; and how many such points the Government estimates there will be by the end of 2017.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","8863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757808","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>The time taken to charge an electric vehicle depends on the type of charge point used and on the vehicle’s on-board charger. Charging rates vary from slow chargers which can take more than 12 hours to recharge a battery completely to rapid chargers which can recharge 80% of the battery in 20-30 minutes.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-12T08:38:56.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757808/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757808/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757808/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Electric Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his Department's most recent estimate is of the average time taken to recharge an electric car.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","8864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757809","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government aims to ensure that trade will continue to be as frictionless as possible, so that the effects on businesses using the Port of Dover and the Channel Tunnel are minimised. The Department for Transport is working closely with the Treasury, HMRC and other Departments towards that end.</p><p> </p><p>The discussion paper on <em>Future customs arrangements, </em>published in August, set out our positive commitment to trade with the EU and options for ensuring that the customs system is as facilitative as possible.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-12T12:04:38.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757809/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757809/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757809/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Freight: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect on businesses using the Port of Dover and the Channel Tunnel of the reintroduction of customs procedures between the EU and the UK; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","8818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757810","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>Operation Stack is a multi-agency approach designed to reduce traffic disruption resulting from issues affecting the cross-Channel crossings. The effects of its implementation are unique to the individual circumstances and duration of its deployment, and so no reliable assessment of the general effects of Operation Stack can be undertaken in advance.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-13T11:34:31.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757810/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757810/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757810/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","M20: Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of the implementation of Operation Stack on the (a) UK economy and (b) Kent economy and (c) logistics industry; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","8819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757811","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>An impact assessment was published in 2014 prior to implementation, which outlined the potential costs and benefits of the change. A copy of the impact assessment can be accessed at the following link:</p><p><a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukia/2014/426" target="_blank">http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukia/2014/426</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-12T08:50:30.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757811/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757811/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757811/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Motor Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what cost-benefit analysis his Department has made of eliminating paper road tax discs.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","8858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757812","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>Highways England recently published their 2017/18 Delivery Plan which provides updates on schemes from 2015 to 2020. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/642750/Highways_England_Delivery_Plan_Update_2017-2018.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/642750/Highways_England_Delivery_Plan_Update_2017-2018.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-12T09:01:25.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757812/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757812/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757812/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Ports: Roads","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to invest in road networks around UK ports in the next two years to prepare for the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","8821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757813","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department for Transport is working closely with other Departments and in consultation with the ports and logistics industry, in order to help ensure that movement through ports and across borders is as frictionless as possible, whatever the outcome of negotiations on future arrangements for trade with the EU.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-12T10:24:50.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757813/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757813/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757813/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Customs: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure that fluidity of movement through ports and across borders is maintained when the UK leaves the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","8820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757814","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>The Government has not undertaken a formal assessment. While the Government acknowledges that any changes to arrangements for EU workers will be a factor in the availability of skilled staff for road haulage, it is not the only factor. As noted in the Government’s response to the Transport Committee’s report on skills and workforce planning in the road haulage sector, there are encouraging signs. For example there were about 10,000 more HGV driving test passes in 2015/16 compared to two years before, in response to the higher demand for HGV drivers and the shortages. In addition the industry has developed a new Trailblazer Apprenticeship standard for HGV drivers to be funded through the Apprenticeship Levy.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-13T15:01:28.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757814/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757814/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757814/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Logistics: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of possible reductions in skilled immigration from the EU into the road-based logistics sector; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","8822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757815","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>Pending Transport for the North’s formal establishment as the first statutory Sub-national Transport Body, co-operation on investment planning takes place through our existing partnership with Rail North.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has not made any changes to our upgrade plans for the Transpennine Route. We are currently working with Rail North and Network Rail to develop very significant improvements for rail passengers on this route with phased introduction from December 2022. These could be the result of investment in new trains, electrification or other infrastructure work. The options will be costed by December, ahead of a decision next year.</p><p> </p><p>The upgrade aims to deliver major reductions in journey times (such as a target time of 40 minutes for fast trains from Manchester to Leeds, and 62 minutes from Manchester to York), the ability to run more frequent and longer trains offering more seats on both long distance and local services and improvements to overall performance on the whole route. There has been no change in these ambitions.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-11T15:51:17.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757815/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757815/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757815/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Railways: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he had with Transport for the North in advance of his announcement that the full electrification of the Transpennine route between Leeds and Manchester would no longer take place.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","8935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757816","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>The Government does not propose to conduct a review of the capacity of Swindon rail station at the present time. We will continue to engage with Network Rail’s route utilisation strategy for work programmes for the period starting in April 2019.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-13T11:41:18.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757816/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757816/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757816/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Swindon Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will conduct a review of the capacity of Swindon rail station.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","8895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757817","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>Train Operating Companies are continuing to fit Wi-Fi on trains. Based upon the information received from Train Operating Companies on the fitment of Wi-Fi roughly 50% of trains have equipment installed, which is a two-thirds increase from the position at the start of 2016.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-12T14:12:12.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757817/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757817/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757817/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Railways: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the availability of WiFi across the rail network.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","8893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757818","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>We are committed to putting passengers at the heart of everything we do and want them to have a stronger voice. As part of this, we are fully supportive of the introduction of an independent Rail Ombudsman to investigate and rule on unresolved rail passenger complaints.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-12T14:21:17.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757818/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757818/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757818/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Public Transport: Ombudsman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to create a Public Transport Ombudsman.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","8896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757819","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>Ministers in the Department for Transport have not had any recent discussions with Home Office Ministers on this subject. However, officials in DfT, DVLA, the Police and the Home Office have day to day contact about a multitude of road safety issues, including unlicensed driving in all its forms.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-13T11:37:23.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757819/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757819/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757819/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Driving: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with the Home Secretary on tackling banned drivers who continue to drive.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","8951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757820","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>Following our public consultation on drones, we announced in July our intention to introduce a registration scheme and mandatory competency testing for all users of drones weighing 250g or more. In doing so, we will increase the accountability of these users and improve their awareness of the rules and regulations, helping to reduce the misuse of drones and protect public safety, security and privacy. Furthermore, anyone using a drone of 250g and above will receive, at minimum, online training on how to fly safely and then be required to pass a short knowledge test in order to prove they have understood the rules.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently considering legislative vehicles to deliver these measures and what further steps may need to be taken.</p><p> </p><p>We will be working with the Civil Aviation Authority and industry partners to develop the detailed standards and requirements for these two policies, to ensure effective and robust systems are put in place, and intend to provide an update soon.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-13T16:23:09.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757820/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757820/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757820/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to introduce proposals for (a) mandatory registration of drones and (b) safety courses for owners of drones.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","8962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757821","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>Utility companies, contractors and other works promoters already have to pay for mobile traffic lights and any other traffic management equipment that may be required for a particular work site. Not all works need mobile traffic lights.</p><p> </p><p>My Department published a consultation on lane rental on 2<sup>nd</sup> September. Lane rental allows local authorities to charge for works on the busiest roads at the busiest times. Charges are set to reflect the cost of congestion and disruption to road users rather than the type of traffic control used, and can be up to £2,500 per day.</p><p> </p><p>The consultation is open until 28<sup>th</sup> October. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-of-lane-rental-schemes-for-roadworks" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-of-lane-rental-schemes-for-roadworks</a></p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-12T09:10:13.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757821/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757821/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757821/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Traffic Lights: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to include the ability to charge for the installation of mobile traffic lights in his proposals to allow local authorities to reclaim income from constructors for disruption to roads.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","8950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757822","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>The route into Sheffield from the south will be electrified from Clay Cross Junction by 2033 for HS2 services from London.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State confirmed this intention in the Houses of Parliament in July.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-11T14:13:04.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757822/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757822/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757822/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Midland Main Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the cancellation of the Midland Mainline electrification on the ability of High Speed 2 to integrate with the existing rail network.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","8931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757823","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>Following our public consultation on drones, we announced in July our intention to introduce a registration scheme and mandatory competency testing for all users of drones weighing 250g or more. In doing so, we will increase the accountability of these users and improve their awareness of the rules and regulations, helping to reduce the misuse of drones and protect public safety, security and privacy. Furthermore, anyone using a drone of 250g and above will receive, at minimum, online training on how to fly safely and then be required to pass a short knowledge test in order to prove they have understood the rules.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently considering legislative vehicles to deliver these measures and what further steps may need to be taken.</p><p> </p><p>We will be working with the Civil Aviation Authority and industry partners to develop the detailed standards and requirements for these two policies, to ensure effective and robust systems are put in place, and intend to provide an update soon.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-13T16:19:52.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757823/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757823/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757823/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Unmanned Air Vehicles: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to require the registration of drones.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","8980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757824","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>In the 2016-2017 financial year, Network Rail contracted out the following work by value, in relation to maintenance, renewals and enhancements:</p><p> </p><ul><li>In relation to maintenance in 2016-17 accounted for 16.6% of the total maintenance spend by Network Rail in year.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>In relation to renewals in 2016-17 accounted for 60.5% of the total renewals spend by Network Rail in year.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>In relation to enhancements in 2016-17 accounted for 78.3% of the total enhancements spend by Network Rail in year.</li></ul><p> </p><p>Breakdowns of the reported profit of Network Rail’s external sub-contractors, and data relating to any incremental costs from external contracting is not held by Network Rail.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-11T14:56:16.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757824/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757824/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757824/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Network Rail: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of Network Rail's work by value was outsourced to external firms in the 2016-17 financial year; what the total value of that work was on (a) maintenance, (b) renewals and (c) enhancements; what the total profit to external firms from those contracts was for (i) maintenance, (ii) renewals and (iii) enhancements; and what the total additional cost resulting from multiple tiers of external contractors duplicating project management functions was relating to (A) maintenance, (B) renewals and (C) enhancements.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","8932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757825","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>The forecast costs of delivering the cancelled electrification on (a) was around £0.5bn, (b) around £1.2bn and (c) around £40m (all in cash prices).</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-11T16:46:57.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757825/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757825/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757825/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Railways: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the projected cost was of the cancelled electrification on the (a) Great Western Mainline, (b) Midland Mainline and (c) the line between Windermere and Oxenholme.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","8933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757826","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>New technologies mean that we can improve journeys for passengers sooner than expected with state of the art trains, instead of carrying out disruptive electrification works along these routes.</p><p> </p><p>Around £50m has been spent to date on development of the first three schemes. An investment decision will be made early next year on the Transpennine Route Upgrade, which is currently in the development phase. We are continuing to develop all options for this major route upgrade and have spent around £100m including delivering an improvement at Micklefield in West Yorkshire at Easter of this year which will improve reliability and train performance.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-11T16:49:30.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757826/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757826/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757826/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Railways: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much has been spent to date on the planned electrification of the (a) Midland Mainline north of Kettering to Sheffield and Nottingham, (b) Great Western route west of Cardiff, (c) line between Windermere and Oxenholme and (d) Transpennine route between Manchester and Leeds.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","8934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757827","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-13","<p>The effectiveness of both low emission zones and congestion zone charging in reducing levels of nitrogen dioxide (NO<sub>2</sub>) has been considered in the ‘Evidence review on effectiveness of transport measures in reducing nitrogen dioxide’ (Defra and Ricardo Energy &amp; Environment, 2016), which is available online at: <a href="https://uk-air.defra.gov.uk/" target="_blank">uk-air.defra.gov.uk</a>.</p><p>The UK plan for tackling roadside NO<sub>2</sub> is clear that a range of measures which improve air quality could also reduce congestion, including improving local bus services and changing road layouts at pinch points.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-09-13T09:11:51.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757827/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757827/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757827/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-05","Tolls: Pollution Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of congestion zone charging in reducing levels of nitrogen oxide.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","8941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757828","Wales Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>Nothing.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2017-09-12T09:53:38.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757828/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757828/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757828/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-09-05","Wales Office: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how much his Department has paid in letting fees for its estate in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8786"
